codelist.label: Plot Activity Value
codelist.definition: The economic activity executed on the plot, as coded accoring to EU regulation (EC) 1200/2009, annex II, chapter 2. (codes 2.01 - 2.04.07 and 2.06.03 -2.06.04).

extensibility.label: Extensible with values at any level

value.label: 2_01_01_Cereals for the production of grain (including seed)
value.definition: 2_01_07_Fresh vegetables, melons and strawberries of which:

value.label: 2_01_01_01_Common wheat and spelt
value.definition: 2_01_08_Flowers and ornamental plants (excluding nurseries)

value.label: 2_01_01_02_Durum wheat
value.definition: 2_06_Mushrooms, energy crops and genetically modified crops

value.label: 2_01_01_03_Rye
value.definition: Secale cereale L., including mixtures of rye and other cereals sown in the autumn (maslin).

value.label: 2_01_01_04_Barley
value.definition: Hordeum vulgare L.

value.label: 2_01_01_05_Oats
value.definition: Avena sativa L., including mixtures of oats and other cereals sown in the spring.

value.label: 2_01_01_06_Grain maize
value.definition: Maize (Zea mays L.) harvested for grain.

value.label: 2_01_01_07_Rice
value.definition: Oryza sativa L.

value.label: 2_01_01_99_Other cereals for the production of grain
value.definition: Cereals sown in pure crops, harvested dry for grain, and that are not recorded elsewhere under the previous items.

value.label: 2_01_02_Dried pulses and protein crops for the production of grain (including seed and mixtures of cereals and pulses)
value.definition: Crops sown and harvested mainly for their protein content.
value.description: All areas of dried pulses and protein crops harvested dry for grain, regardless of use, shall be recorded here (including crops used for renewable energy production).

value.label: 2_01_02_01_Dried pulses and protein crops of which peas, field beans and sweet lupins
value.definition: Pisum sativum L., Vicia faba L., Lupinus spp., sown in pure crops, harvested dry for grain.

value.label: 2_01_03_Potatoes (including early potatoes and seed potatoes)
value.definition: Solanum tuberosum L.

value.label: 2_01_04_Sugar beet (excluding seed)
value.definition: Beta vulgaris L. intended for the sugar industry and alcohol production (including energy production).

value.label: 2_01_05_Fodder roots and brassicas (excluding seed)
value.definition: Fodder beet (Beta vulgaris L.) and plants of the Brassicae family harvested mainly for animal feed, regardless whether it is the root or the stem, and other plants cultivated mainly for their roots for fodder, not mentioned elsewhere.

value.label: 2_01_06_Industrial crops
value.definition: Crops that are normally not sold directly for consumption because they need to be industrially processed prior to final use.
value.description: All harvested areas of industrial crops, regardless of use, shall be recorded here (including crops used for renewable energy production).

value.label: 2_01_06_01_Tobacco
value.definition: Nicotiana tabacum L.

value.label: 2_01_06_02_Hops
value.definition: Humulus lupulus L.

value.label: 2_01_06_03_Cotton
value.definition: Gossypium spp., harvested for fibre as well as for oil-seeds.

value.label: 2_01_06_04_Rape and turnip rape
value.definition: Brassica napus L. (partim) and Brassica rapa L. var. sylvestris (Lam.) Briggs, grown for the production of oil, harvested as dry grains.

value.label: 2_01_06_05_Sunflower
value.definition: Helianthus annuus L., harvested as dry grains.

value.label: 2_01_06_06_Soya
value.definition: Glycine max L. Merril, harvested as dry grains.

value.label: 2_01_06_07_Linseed (oil flax)
value.definition: Linum usitatissimum L., varieties grown mainly for producing oil, harvested as dry grains.

value.label: 2_01_06_08_Other oil seed crops
value.definition: Other crops grown mainly for their oil content, harvested as dry grains, which are not mentioned elsewhere.

value.label: 2_01_06_09_Flax
value.definition: Linum usitatissimum L., varieties grown mainly for producing fibre.

value.label: 2_01_06_10_Hemp
value.definition: Cannabis sativa L.

value.label: 2_01_06_11_Other fibre crops
value.definition: Other plants grown mainly for their fibre content, not mentioned elsewhere.

value.label: 2_01_06_12_Aromatic plants, medicinal and culinary plants
value.definition: Plants or parts of plants for pharmaceutical purposes, perfume manufacture or human consumption.
value.description: Culinary plants are distinguished from vegetables in that they are used in small amounts and provide flavour rather than substance to food.

value.label: 2_01_06_99_Other industrial crops not mentioned elsewhere
value.definition: Other industrial crops that have not been mentioned elsewhere.
value.description: Areas of crops used exclusively for renewable energy production are included.

value.label: 2_01_07_Fresh vegetables, melons and strawberries of which:
value.definition: Fresh vegetables, melons and strawberries

value.label: 2_01_07_01_Outdoor or under low (not accessible) protective cover
value.definition: Fresh vegetables, melons and strawberries, outdoor or under low (non-accessible) cover.

value.label: 2_01_07_01_01_Open field
value.definition: Fresh vegetables, melons and strawberries grown on arable land in rotation with other agricultural crops.

value.label: 2_01_07_01_02_Market gardening
value.definition: Fresh vegetables, melons and strawberries grown on arable land in rotation with other horticultural crops.

value.label: 2_01_07_02_Under glass or other (accessible) protective cover
value.definition: Crops, which for the whole of their period of growth or for the predominant part of it are covered by greenhouses or fixed or mobile high cover (glass or rigid or flexible plastic).

value.label: 2_01_08_Flowers and ornamental plants (excluding nurseries)
value.definition: Flowers and ornamental plants (excluding nurseries)

value.label: 2_01_08_01_Outdoor or under low (not accessible) protective cover
value.definition: Flowers and ornamental plants (excluding nurseries), outdoor or under low (not accessible) protective cover.

value.label: 2_01_08_02_Under glass or other (accessible) protective cover
value.definition: Flowers and ornamental plants (excluding nurseries), which for the whole of their period of growth or for the predominant part of it are covered by greenhouses or fixed or mobile high cover (glass or rigid or flexible plastic).

value.label: 2_01_09_Plants harvested green
value.definition: All green arable crops intended mainly for animal feed, grown in rotation with other crops and occupying the same parcel for less than five years (annual or multiannual fodder crops).
value.description: Green crops used for renewable energy production are included. Crops not used on the holding but sold, either for direct use on other agricultural holdings or to industry, are included.

value.label: 2_01_09_01_Temporary grass
value.definition: Grass plants for grazing, hay or silage included as a part of a normal crop rotation, lasting at least one crop year and less than five years, sown with grass or grass mixtures. The areas are broken up by ploughing or other tilling or the plants are destroyed by other means such as by herbicides before they are sown again.
value.description: Mixtures of predominantly grass plants and other forage crops (usually leguminous), grazed, harvested green or as dried hay are included here.

value.label: 2_01_09_02_Other plants harvested green
value.definition: Other annual or multiannual (less than five years) fodder crops.

value.label: 2_01_09_02_01_Green maize
value.definition: All forms of maize (Zea mays L.) grown mainly for silage, which is not harvested for grain (whole cob, parts of or whole plant).
value.description: This includes green maize directly consumed by animals (without silage) and whole cobs (grain, rachis, husk) harvested for feedstuff or silage as well as for renewable energy production.

value.label: 2_01_09_02_02_Leguminous plants
value.definition: Leguminous plants grown and harvested green as the whole plant mainly for forage.
value.description: Mixtures of predominantly leguminous (normally > 80 %) forage crops and grass plants, harvested green or as dried hay are included here.

value.label: 2_01_09_02_99_Other plants harvested green not mentioned elsewhere
value.definition: Other arable crops intended mainly for animal fodder, harvested green, not mentioned elsewhere.

value.label: 2_01_10_Arable land seed and seedlings
value.definition: Areas producing seeds and seedlings for sale, excluding cereals, rice, pulses, potatoes and oil seeds.

value.label: 2_01_11_Other arable land crops
value.definition: Arable crops not included elsewhere.

value.label: 2_01_12_Fallow land
value.definition: All arable land included in the crop rotation system, whether worked or not, but with no intention to produce a harvest for the duration of a crop year.
value.description: The essential characteristic offallow land is that it is left torecover, normally for the wholeof a crop year.Fallow land may be:1. bare land bearing no cropsat all;2. land with spontaneousnatural growth, which may beused as feed or ploughed in;3. land sown exclusively forthe production of greenmanure (green fallow).

value.label: 2_02_Kitchen gardens
value.definition: Areas devoted to the cultivation of agricultural products intended for self-consumption by the holder and his household, normally separated off from the rest of the agricultural land, and recognisable as kitchen gardens.
value.description: Only occasional surplusproducts coming from thisarea are sold off from theholding. All areas from whichproducts are consistently soldon the market belong underother items, even if part of theproduction is consumed by theholder and his household.

value.label: 2_03_Permanent grassland
value.definition: Land used permanently (for five years or more) to grow herbaceous forage crops, through cultivation (sown) or naturally (self-seeded), and that is not included in the crop rotation on the holding.
value.description: The land can be used forgrazing or mown for silage,hay or used for renewableenergy production.

value.label: 2_03_01_Permanent grassland Pasture and meadow, excluding rough grazings
value.definition: Permanent pasture on good or medium quality soils. These areas can normally be used for intensive grazing.

value.label: 2_03_02_Permanent grassland Rough grazings
value.definition: Low yielding permanent grassland, usually on low quality soil, for example on hilly land and at high altitudes, usually unimproved by fertiliser, cultivation, reseeding or drainage.
value.description: These areas can normally beused only for extensivegrazing and are not normallymown or are mown in anextensive manner; they cannotsupport a large density ofanimals.

value.label: 2_03_03_Permanent grassland no longer used for production purposes and eligible for the payment of subsidies
value.definition: Areas of permanent grassland and meadows no longer used for production purposes which, in line with Regulation (EC) No 1782/2003 or, where applicable, the most recent legislation, are maintained in good agricultural and environmental condition and are eligible for financial support.

value.label: 2_04_Permanent crops
value.definition: Crops not grown in rotation, other than permanent grassland, which occupy the soil for a long period and yield crops over several years.

value.label: 2_04_01_Fruit and berry plantations
value.definition: Areas containing trees, bushes and perennial berry plants other than strawberries for the production of fruit. Orchards may be of the continuous type with minimum spacing between trees or of the non-continuous type with wide spacing.

value.label: 2_04_01_01_Fruit species, of which:
value.definition: Fruit tree plantations which are traditionally cropped for producing fruits.

value.label: 2_04_01_01_01_Fruit of temperate climate zones
value.definition: Fruit tree plantations which are traditionally cropped in temperate climates for producing fruits.

value.label: 2_04_01_01_02_Fruit of subtropical climate zones
value.definition: Fruit tree plantations which are traditionally cropped in subtropical climates for producing fruits.

value.label: 2_04_01_02_Berry species
value.definition: Berry plantations which are traditionally cropped both in temperate and subtropical climates for producing berries.

value.label: 2_04_01_03_Nuts
value.definition: Nut tree plantations which are traditionally cropped in temperate and subtropical climates.

value.label: 2_04_02_Citrus plantations
value.definition: Plantations of Citrus spp.

value.label: 2_04_03_Olive plantations
value.definition: Plantations of Olea europea L.

value.label: 2_04_03_01_Normally producing table olives
value.definition: Plantations of varieties normally grown for producing table olives.

value.label: 2_04_03_02_/Normally producing olives for oil production
value.definition: Plantations of varieties normally grown for producing olive oil.

value.label: 2_04_04_Vineyards, of which normally producing:
value.definition: Plantations of Vitis vinifera L_

value.label: 2_04_04_01_Quality wine
value.definition: Grape varieties normally grown for the production of wines with a protected designation of origin (PDO) which comply with the requirements (i) of Council Regulation (EC) No 479/2008(1) or, where applicable, the most recent legislation; and (ii) the corresponding national rules.
value.description: Grape varieties normally grown for the production of wines with a protected geographical indication (PGI) which comply with the requirements (i) of Regulation (EC) No 479/2008 or, where applicable, the most recent legislation; and (ii) the corresponding national rules.

value.label: 2_04_04_02_Other wines
value.definition: Grape varieties normally grown for the production of wines other than PDO and PGI wines.

value.label: 2_04_04_03_Table grapes
value.definition: Grape varieties normally grown for the production of fresh grapes.

value.label: 2_04_04_04_Raisins
value.definition: Grape varieties normally grown for the production of raisins.

value.label: 2_04_05_Nurseries
value.definition: Areas of young ligneous (woody) plants grown in the open air for subsequent transplantation:
value.description: (a) vine and root-stocknurseries;(b) fruit tree and berriesnurseries;(c) ornamental nurseries;(d) commercial nurseries offorest trees (excluding thosefor the holdings ownrequirements grown withinwoodland);(e) trees and bushes forplanting in gardens, parks, atthe roadside and onembankments (e.g. hedgerowplants, rose trees and otherornamental bushes,ornamental conifers), includingin all cases their stocks andyoung seedlings.

value.label: 2_04_06_Other permanent crops
value.definition: Open-air permanent crops other than those under the previous heading and in particular those used for plaiting or weaving, harvested generally every year.

value.label: 2_04_06_01_Other permanent crops of which Christmas trees(1)
value.definition: Trees planted for commercial purposes as Christmas trees on the utilised agricultural area.

value.label: 2_04_07_Permanent crops under glass
value.definition: Permanent crops under glass

value.label: 2_06_Mushrooms, energy crops and genetically modified crops
value.definition: Mushrooms, energy crops and genetically modified crops

value.label: 2_06_01_Mushrooms
value.definition: Cultivated mushrooms grown in buildings which have been specially erected or adapted for growing mushrooms, as well as in underground premises, caves and cellars.

value.label: 2_06_03_Energy crops (for the production of biofuels or other renewable energy)
value.definition: The production area of energy crops benefiting from the following support schemes under Regulation (EC) No 1782/2003:

value.label: 2_06_03_01_Energy crops of which on set-aside area
value.definition: The production area of energy crops benefiting of the payment linked to set-aside entitlement when production takes place on set-aside area (Council Regulation (EC) No 1782/2003, Article 55 or 56)

value.label: 2_06_04_Genetically modified crops
value.definition: Genetically modified crops (GMC) mean any organism as defined in Article 2 of Council Directive 2001/18/EC(1) OJ L 106, 17.4.2001, p. 1. (1) or, where applicable, the most recent legislation.
